        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <font face='Tahoma'>My best advice for soloing the bank would be doing so in the fear hall.  Yes, Captain Bvellos does path through this area but like Dryzza said every hour, you should always keep an eye out for him, when you see him just feign, he won't agro your pet and he will walk on up his path to the arena.  He'll stay up in the arena for about 10 minutes or so and then path back down.  I usually take a break from the bank while he is on his path just to med up or recover from a bad fight.</P><P>To answer Kallu, you will have some problems soloing the bank at 54 due to agro from other giants when you pull.  I wasn't able to solo pull the whole bank until 57 where sargents would agro me if I pulled a nearby watchmen.</P><P>[60 Warlock] Natibela (Gnome)  <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle>  <img src=icon_smile_wink.gif border=0 align=middle>  <img src=icon_smile_shy.gif border=0 align=middle><BR>The Seventh Hammer</font id='Tahoma'><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
