        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=81892&amp;TOPIC_ID=8979&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=soloing+4+torn+enchanted+silk+robe&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         A few more tidbits about the bank camp:</P><P>--  Bank spawns come in three flavors:  watchmen (most common, lb to 60), sergeants (db to 60), and lieutenants (least common, db to 60).  Lieutenants are the only mobs that drop armor.<BR>--  There are eight wm/sg/lt spawns outside the bank.  Two along the wall between the passage to EW and the arena ramp, two near the bank itself, and two on the path leading down to WL.  There are two wanderers:  one paths from the bank down to WL zone and back, one paths from the bank up to the arena and back.  Any of these eight spawns can be lieutentants (armor droppers).<BR>--  There are three more wm/sg/lt spawns inside the bank.  HOWEVER if you pull the bank you will get two named adds:  Staff Sergeant Drioc and one of Captain Bvellos or Kael Militia Captain (the PH for Bvellos).  Both summon and are casters.  Bottom line:  though you can get three more spawns by FD pulling, if you're soloing the three inside the bank aren't really worth it.<BR>--  Captain Bvellos, if he is up, will roam from the bank up to the arena and back.  His PH, the Kael Militia Captain, does not roam.  Bottom line:  The camp is easier when Bvellos is not up.  If he is up, watch carefully and FD as soon as you see him (he hits in the mid to upper 200s).  I usually check whether Bvellos is up before I start.<BR>--  This camp is easiest to do fearkiting.  If you snare and fear a mob on the ramp between the arena area and the bank area, it will walk down the ramp, turn around at the bottom, and walk back up again.<BR>--  To break the camp, you need to kill the wanderer (the one that goes from the bank to the arena).  Also, a feared mob will get close enough at the bottom of its fear path to aggro the first spawn on the wall between the ramp and the passage to EW.  I usually do the wanderer and the first wall spawn at the same time to break the camp (it's easy if you have both invoke fear and trepidation memmed).  Another alternative is backing your pet off before the mob reaches the bottom of the ramp, as another poster suggested. <BR>--  This camp is very streaky; sometimes you will get several armor drops in a few hours, and sometimes you will get no armor drops all day.  The average is probably one piece per 3-4 hours.  Robes and BPs are MUCH rarer.<BR>--  If you are level 60 you will certainly kill all 8 spawns before repop.  If you get bored you can always kill the guards and senior guards that spawn at the top of the ramp (occasionally you will get a senior guard that is unfearable, but it's pretty rare).</P><P>This is a good camp for faction and farming armor drops.  It is NOT a good exp camp.  It is also NOT the fastest way to get a robe--your odds of a BP drop are MUCH better with the Legos and Vets that spawn in the arena.</P><P>Nahaz Millithor<BR>Warlock, Seekers of Unity <BR>Solusek Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
